    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town was first settled around 1800 after General John Sullivan ordered the removal of Indians in 1799.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://newfieldny.org/local-information/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Eliakim Dean erected Newfield’s first saw mill in 1809, sparking the town’s early industrial growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://newfieldny.org/local-information/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Newfield Hamlet incorporated as a village in 1895, then dissolved on December 31, 1927, returning all services to the town.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newfield_(CDP)%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The hamlet sits near the center of the town, southwest of Ithaca, at coordinates 42°21′43″N 76°35′32″W.",
